<div class="challenges-summary">
  <!-- Header Image -->
  <%= image_tag("waste.jpeg", class: 'challenges-header-img') %>
  <div class="image-overlay"></div>
  <div class="challenges-desc">
    <h1>BODY</h1>
    <p>No governing body, not even the FDA, conducts pre-market safety testing on the ingredients in our personal
      care products. If you’re wondering how your conditioner promises silky hair and your deodorant pledges
      18 hour staying power, the answer is those unregulated chemicals. Our skin absorbs 60% of EVERYTHING we put on it.
       We have to be our own judges of safety when it comes to what we put on our body. Opt for products that are
       free of toxic ingredients and hold themselves to higher standards than the FDA.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="all-challenges">
  <div class="challenges-header">CHALLENGES</div>
  <div class="accordion" id="challenge-accordion">

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
        <h5 class="mb-0">
          <!-- Challenge header -->
          <button class="accordion-toggle btn btn-link" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
            SHOP ORGANIC
          </button>
        </h5>
      </div>

      <!-- Collapsible challenge body -->
      <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#challenge-accordion">
        <div class="card-body container">
          <div class="row">
            <div src="" class="col-md-2">
              <%= image_tag("placeholder.png", size: '100x100') %>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body-text col-md-10">
              <div>
                According to the Campaign for Safe Cosmetics, a project of the Breast Cancer Fund, women use an average
                 of 12 personal care products a day, while men use an average of 6. With this kind of regular product use,
                 it means we potentially expose ourselves to hundreds of individual and potentially toxic chemical
                 ingredients daily. Read the ingredient labels on the bodycare products that you use (e.g. body wash,
                 shampoo, hand soap). Use the Think Dirty App or Campaign for Safe Cosmetics Red List to check its
                 overall hazard rating. Which ingredients are potentially hazardous? Shop for an organic alternative
                 online or at a local grocer when you run out of your current supply of bodycare products.
              </div>

              <div class="learn-more">
                <p class="learn-more-header">Learn more</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="http://www.safecosmetics.org/get-the-facts/chemicals-of-concern/red-list/">Red list</a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="https://www.thinkdirtyapp.com/">Think Dirty App</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="challenge-duration">
                <p class="learn-more-header">How long do you want to take the challenge for?</p>
                <form>
                  <div class="form-row">
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="3">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <select class="form-control" id="inputInterval">
                        <option>Choose interval</option>
                        <option>day(s)</option>
                        <option>week(s)</option>
                        <option>month(s)</option>
                      </select>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </form>
              </div>

              <button class="get-started-btn">
                GET STARTED ON THIS CHALLENGE!
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
        <h5 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-toggle btn btn-link collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
            MAKE YOUR OWN
          </button>
        </h5>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#challenge-accordion">
        <div class="card-body container">
          <div class="row">
            <div src="" class="col-md-2">
              <%= image_tag("placeholder.png", size: '100x100') %>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-10">
              <div>
                Even if you read the ingredient labels before purchasing products, you may not be getting the whole story.
                A single ingredient, like “synthetic fragrance”, can actually contain hundreds of different ingredients
                with proven health risks. In fact, in the United States, no government mandates require that the
                ingredients found in “fragrance” or “parfum” be listed on the package or anywhere else for that matter
                – which translates into a serious lack of transparency to YOU! Pick up one of your favorite personal
                care products and investigate the ingredients used to make it. Making your own bath and body products
                ensures total transparency – you get to know exactly what is in your product because you made it!
                Plus you’ll be creating less waste by reducing packaging. The cherry on top? You’ll probably end up
                saving some money. Think about a product that you use most often, and make it yourself!
              </div>
              <div class="learn-more">
                <p class="learn-more-header">Learn more</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="https://www.thinkdirtyapp.com/">Think Dirty App</a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="https://dontmesswithmama.com/100-diy-beauty-recipes/">DIY Recipes</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="challenge-duration">
                <p class="learn-more-header">How long do you want to take the challenge for?</p>
                <form>
                  <div class="form-row">
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="3">
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
                      <select class="form-control" id="inputInterval">
                        <option>Choose interval</option>
                        <option>day(s)</option>
                        <option>week(s)</option>
                        <option>month(s)</option>
                      </select>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </form>
              </div>

              <div class="get-started-btn">
                GET STARTED ON THIS CHALLENGE!
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
